### constructCallSiteEntryDIE() {#a3f002d26ef8a98b14c82c510d49e26b2}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>DIE &amp; DwarfCompileUnit::constructCallSiteEntryDIE (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> &amp; ScopeDIE, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/disubprogram">DISubprogram</a> &#42; CalleeSP, bool IsTail, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsymbol">MCSymbol</a> &#42; PCAddr, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsymbol">MCSymbol</a> &#42; CallAddr, unsigned CallReg)</>}>
Construct a call site entry <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/die">DIE</a> describing a call within <code>Scope</code> to a callee described by <code>CalleeSP</code>.

<code>IsTail</code> specifies whether the call is a tail call. <code>PCAddr</code> points to the PC value after the call instruction. <code>CallAddr</code> points to the PC value at the call instruction (or is null). <code>CallReg</code> is a register location for an indirect call. For direct calls the <code>CallReg</code> is set to 0.
